1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:11,000
Oh, I have second thoughts about one of the shirts I packed.

2
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:14,000
The blue one with the stripes.

3
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:16,000
I'm sure it's fine. It's a blue shirt.

4
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:19,000
Oh, yeah, but I'm wondering if it's too blue.

5
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:23,000
Like, am I making a statement with the blueness?

6
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:27,000
I am leaving early today for Philly.

7
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:31,000
Because tomorrow is the first day of my new job.

8
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:36,000
So I figure I'd get in at five, check in at a hotel about six,

9
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:40,000
so I can get a real good night of restless sleep, nervous puking.

10
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:42,000
Excuse me, trying to get work done?

11
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:46,000
Some people don't care about Jim's new sports job and philla-whatever?

12
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:48,000
So you know my job has something to do with sports,

13
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:51,000
but you don't know the end of the word Philadelphia.

14
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:55,000
Philadelphia, from the Greek, philia meaning love,

15
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:58,000
and Adolf meaning Adolf, the city that loves Adolf.

16
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:00,000
Good luck with your new enterprise.

17
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:02,000
And don't wear the blue striped shirt.

18
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:05,000
It makes your neck look like an old mop handle.

19
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:11,000
Oh, hey guys, the Christmas party is today.

20
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:13,000
Merry Christmas, everyone!

21
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:14,000
No, is it?

22
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:17,000
I mean, it says Xmas party, but I think we all know what that's code for.

23
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:20,000
So we're not going to have a Christmas party this year?

24
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:22,000
Angela, how could you do this to us?

25
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:26,000
Oh, right, like I'm responsible because I'm in charge of the party planning committee.

26
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:28,000
Well, you are the one in charge of it.

27
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:30,000
Don't blame me for something we all forgot.

28
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:32,000
Let's not blame her for something we all forgot.

29
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:36,000
I didn't realize how many of Angela's opinions I agreed with

30
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:40,000
until she tried to have my kneecap shattered for sleeping with her husband.

31
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:42,000
She makes a lot of very sound points.

32
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:46,000
I knew the party was today, but nobody asked me to plan it, so I didn't.

33
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:48,000
Funny how that works.

34
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:52,000
We're out there sweating our balls off every day, busting our balls.

35
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:54,000
We deserve a Christmas party.

36
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:58,000
Well, then why don't we just get some liquor and those mini cupcakes?

37
00:01:58,000 --> 00:01:59,000
Mini cupcakes?

38
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:05,000
As in the mini version of regular cupcakes, which is already a mini version of cake?

39
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:08,000
Honestly, where does it end with you people?

40
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:10,000
What about an authentic Pennsylvania Dutch Christmas?

41
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:14,000
Drink some Glühwein, enjoy some Hasenfeffer,

42
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:19,000
enjoy Christmas with St. Nicholas's rural German companion, Bouschnickel.

43
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:22,000
Yes, that, that, that.

44
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:24,000
Definitely doing that. Are we all in agreement?

45
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:25,000
No.

46
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:26,000
Done, right?

47
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:28,000
No, I want tropical Christmas.

48
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:30,000
Topless Christmas.

49
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:32,000
Topless Swissmiss.

50
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:34,000
Spanish topless and Swissmiss hot cocoa.

51
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:36,000
What's so hard to understand?

52
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:41,000
Or, who was it that suggested the authentic Pennsylvania Dutch Christmas?

53
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:43,000
I think it was someone really popular.

54
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:44,000
We already said no.

55
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:46,000
No, no, no.

56
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:50,000
This is me and my family celebrating Pennsylvania Dutch Christmas in 1982 on the farm.

57
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:54,000
There's me and my brother Jeb breaking the ceremonial pig rib.

58
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:56,000
He doesn't come back for Christmas anymore.

59
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:59,000
The sepia tint is from an app on my phone.

60
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:02,000
This is the same photo Matrix style.

61
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:05,000
I'm not understanding the confusion.

62
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:11,000
Am I the only one who wants to try Hufflepuffs and Schnauzerhosen and meet this Glenn Pickle guy?

63
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:14,000
Party planning committee, emergency meeting, now.

64
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:18,000
I'm on it.

65
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:22,000
Great. I'm just hoping German terrorists don't take over this Christmas party.

66
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:24,000
They can go all John McLean on their asses.

67
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:27,000
Wait, German terrorists? That's oddly specific.

68
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:30,000
And I think, I think you mean John McCain.

69
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:31,000
Die Hard reference?

70
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:32,000
I haven't seen it.

71
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:34,000
You haven't seen Die Hard?

72
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:36,000
Why haven't you seen Die Hard?

73
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:38,000
I don't know, I just haven't.

74
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:41,000
Come on, you had to have at least seen some of it.

75
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:42,000
Nope.

76
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:45,000
Now, I have a machine gun.

77
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:47,000
Ho, ho, ho.

78
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:50,000
Come out to the coast, we'll get together, have a few laughs.

79
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:52,000
None of this makes any sense to me.

80
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:58,000
Oh yeah, and when he takes the gun off his back and he's like, yippee-ki-yay, motherfuckers.

81
00:03:58,000 --> 00:04:00,000
Actually, he doesn't say that there.

82
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:03,000
He says it earlier when he's on the radio with Hans.

83
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:07,000
Yes, you are right. Forgive me.

84
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:08,000
Well, that's okay, bud.

85
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:09,000
Nope.

86
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:10,000
Common mistake.

87
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:11,000
No, it's not.

88
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:14,000
Nerd! Do you know every line of the movie?

89
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:17,000
My brother dared me to memorize it, and I did.
